  "prompt": "What is the legal framework surrounding money laundering?",
  "response": "The legal framework surrounding money laundering involves multiple levels of legislation and regulations:\n\n1. International Level\n- Financial Action Task Force (FATF) recommendations\n- United Nations Convention Against Transnational Organized Crime\n- International standards for combating financial crimes\n\n2. National Legislation\n- Anti-Money Laundering (AML) laws\n- Bank Secrecy Act\n- Know Your Customer (KYC) regulations\n- Suspicious Activity Reporting requirements\n\n3. Key Legal Components\n- Definition of money laundering offenses\n- Reporting obligations for financial institutions\n- Criminal penalties for violations\n- Asset seizure and forfeiture provisions\n- Enhanced due diligence requirements\n\n4. Regulatory Oversight\n- Financial intelligence units\n- Banking regulators\n- Law enforcement agencies\n- Prosecution mechanisms\n\n5. Compliance Mechanisms\n- Customer identification procedures\n- Transaction monitoring\n- Risk assessment protocols\n- Internal control systems\n\nThe framework aims to prevent, detect, and prosecute financial crimes by establishing comprehensive legal and regulatory standards across jurisdictions.\n\nWould you like me to elaborate on any specific aspect of money laundering legal frameworks?",
